There are several ways to parallelize a neural network. The most common approach is to use multiple processing units, such as CPUs or GPUs, to train the model simultaneously.

For example, if a neural network has a batch size of 128, you could have one processing unit take the first 64 examples in the training set, and another take the next 64 examples, and so on. The processing units would then operate independently and report their progress to a central node that coordinates the parallel computation.

Another way to parallelize a neural network is to use a data parallelism approach. In this approach, each processing unit takes a subset of the data (or a mini-batch within the data) and trains the model using its subsets. The training process then proceeds by moving the subsets from one processing unit to the next in a round-robin fashion until all of the data has been used to train the model.

def sequence_alignment(text, pattern):
    text = text.lower()
    pattern = pattern.lower()
    if len(pattern) > len(text):
        pattern = pattern[:len(text)]

```
def bubble_sort(arr):
    n = len(arr)
    for i in range(n-1):
        sorted = arr[i:n]
        for j in sorted:
            if j < sorted[j+1]:
                temp = arr[j]
                arr[j] = arr[j+1]
                arr[j+1] = temp
    return arr

Despite her youth, Lily understood the importance of having dreams and aspirations, and knew that with hard work and determination, she could accomplish anything she set her mind to.
One day, Lily heard about a magical contest that was taking place in the kingdom. The contest was open to all citizens, and the winner would be granted a special gift that would change their life forever. The prize was a magical ring that would allow the wearer to see beyond the veil of reality and glimpse into the realms that lay beyond.
Lily was intrigued by the idea of seeing beyond the veil and immediately decided that she would enter the contest. With her mother's blessing, Lily set out to write the best story the kingdom had ever seen. She spent day and night crafting a tale of love, hope, and courage, filled with magical creatures and adventures beyond imagination.
As the day of the contest neared, Lily knew that the odds were stacked against her. She was far younger than the other contestants and had never written a story before. But she didn't let that hold her back. With determination in her heart and an unwavering belief in her ability, Lily presented her story to the judges with pride and confidence.
To her surprise, Lily's story was met with rapturous applause and cheers from the crowd. The judges were so moved by her tale that they declared her the winner of the contest, and awarded her the magical ring she had been hoping for.
With her newfound power, Lily ventured into the unknown and explored the realms beyond the veil. She encountered magical creatures and experienced adventures that she had never even dreamed of before. But no matter what she faced, Lily never lost sight of the values that had brought her success in the first place: kindness, compassion, and belief in oneself.
